Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and mildly decreased globulin. Cholesterol and LDL are slightly above the reference range, indicating increased cardiovascular risk. Other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, liver enzymes, and proteins, are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation for renal impairment and cardiovascular risk assessment.
